This is a known breaking change. Android deprecated `AdjustResize` (API 30+), and .NET 10 MAUI adopted **edge-to-edge** rendering by default, which ignores that flag entirely. The fix is to listen to **keyboard insets** and adjust your layout's padding.

### Solution

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Compatibility.Platform.Android;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Bottom padding = keyboard height (minus nav bar already accounted for)
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom - navInsets.Bottom, 0);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return ViewCompat.OnApplyWindowInsets(view, insets);
        }
    }
}
```

### Why this works

| .NET 9 | .NET 10 |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | Edge-to-edge: app draws behind keyboard |
| System handled resizing | You handle `Ime()` insets yourself |

### Tips for your chat layout

- Use a `Grid` with your `CollectionView` in a star-sized row and input bar in an `Auto` row at the bottom — the padding shift will push everything up naturally.
- If you also need this on **iOS**, it already works via `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` — no extra code needed.
- You can check keyboard visibility with `insets.IsVisible(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime())` to trigger animations or scroll-to-bottom.
